.TH NAUTHILUS-DIRECTORCTL 1 "2026-05-26" "nauthilus-director" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nauthilus-directorctl \- control a running Nauthilus Director
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nauthilus-directorctl
.RB [ --address
.IR url ]
.RB [ --timeout
.IR duration ]
.RB [ --output
.IR text|json ]
.IR command
.RI [ arguments ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B nauthilus-directorctl
is the operator CLI for the Director control API.
Every HTTP request is sent through the generated OpenAPI client SDK.
The default output mode is compact key-value text for scripts.
JSON output returns generated response bodies where practical.
.PP
Mutation commands manage runtime state in the running Director.
They do not edit or rewrite YAML configuration files.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --address " " \fIurl\fR
Control API base URL.
The default is
.BR http://127.0.0.1:9090 .
A bare host:port value is interpreted as HTTP.
.TP
.BR --timeout " " \fIduration\fR
Request timeout as a Go duration.
The default is
.BR 5s .
.TP
.BR --output " " \fItext|json\fR
Select output mode.
.TP
.BR --format " " \fItext|json\fR
Alias for
.BR --output
when used before the command name.
For
.B config dump
the command-local
.B --format
flag selects YAML or JSON config serialization.
.TP
.B --version
Print the client version and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B status
Show health, readiness, binary version and API version.
.TP
.B backends list
List backend runtime state.
.TP
.BI "backends show " identifier
Show one backend.
.TP
.BI "backends maintenance enable " identifier " --reason " text
Enable soft maintenance by default.
Use
.BI "--mode " soft|hard
to select maintenance mode and
.BI "--grace-seconds " seconds
when hard maintenance needs an explicit grace value.
.TP
.BI "backends maintenance disable " identifier " --reason " text
Disable backend maintenance.
.TP
.BI "backends out " identifier " --reason " text
Exclude a backend from new runtime placement.
.TP
.BI "backends in " identifier " --reason " text
Return a backend to runtime placement.
.TP
.BI "backends drain " identifier " --mode " soft|hard " --reason " text
Drain a backend.
Use
.BI "--grace-seconds " seconds
to send an explicit grace value.
.TP
.BI "backends weight " identifier " --weight " value " --reason " text
Override the runtime placement weight for one backend.
Use
.B 0
to exclude the backend from new weighted initial placement without terminating
active pins.
.TP
.BI "backends runtime weight " identifier " --weight " value " --reason " text
Alias for
.BR "backends weight" .
.TP
.BI "backends runtime clear " identifier " --reason " text
Clear runtime overrides for one backend.
.TP
.B config dump -d
Read canonical default configuration from the running Director.
.TP
.B config dump -n
Read non-default effective configuration from the running Director.
.TP
.B config dump -d|-n -P
Request protected config output from the running Director by sending the
generated protected config request flag.
If the Director returns
.B 403
the command fails clearly and prints no partial config output.
.TP
.BI "config dump -d|-n --format " yaml|json
Select config document serialization.
YAML is the default.
.TP
.B sessions list --protocol imap
List active sessions, optionally filtered by protocol.
.TP
.BI "sessions show " session-id
Show one active session.
.TP
.BI "sessions kill " session-id " --reason " text
Terminate one active session.
.TP
.B users list
List users with runtime state.
.TP
.BI "users show " user-key
Show one user's runtime state.
.TP
.BI "users sessions " user-key
List sessions for one user.
.TP
.BI "users affinity show " user-key
Show active affinity for one user.
.TP
.BI "users affinity set " user-key " --shard " shard " --reason " text
Set user affinity for future sessions.
.TP
.BI "users affinity clear " user-key " --reason " text
Clear inactive user affinity.
.TP
.BI "users move " user-key " --to-shard " shard " --strategy " strategy " --reason " text
Move future user placement.
Supported strategies are
.BR new_sessions_only ,
.BR kick_existing
and
.BR drain_existing .
.TP
.BI "users kick " user-key " --reason " text
Terminate active sessions for one user.
.TP
.BI "route lookup --protocol imap --user " user-key
Run a side-effect-free route lookup diagnostic.
Optional flags are
.BI "--listener " name
,
.BI "--tenant " tenant
,
.BI "--service-name " name
,
.BI "--backend-pool " pool
,
.B --include-affinity
and repeated
.BI "--attribute " k=v .
Credential-bearing attributes are rejected before the request is sent.
.TP
.B reload
Request a safe runtime reload from the running Director.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
The command succeeded.
.TP
.B 1
The request was sent through the generated client and the server-side operation
failed, or the generated client could not complete the request.
.TP
.B 2
The command line or local client configuration was invalid.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nauthilus-director (1),
.BR nauthilus-director.yaml (5)
